<p><span style="background-color: transparent; color: inherit; font-size: inherit;"><strong>The City Highways Division maintains Stamford's over 315 miles of centerline road, which is the largest municipal road system in the State.</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Crews located at four facilities throughout Stamford handle all the maintenance and repair activities, including but not limited to storm system cleaning, road maintenance, snow plowing, and leaf pickup.</strong></p>
<p><strong>
The Highway team is dedicated to maintaining the wellness of the traveling public as well as the safety and aesthetic value of the infrastructure.</strong></p>
<p>
